## Hypothesis
I will hypothesize that the mutant might behave differently when processing more complex nested JSON structures that heavily utilize spacing or contain unexpected formatting. I predict that these additional formatting aspects could trigger a difference in behavior between the baseline and mutant. To test this, I will use a more complex JSON structure with excessive spacing, nested objects, and arrays, which may interact differently with the regex flags.

## Experiment
```python
from string_utils._regex import JSON_WRAPPER_RE

def test__json_wrapper_re_complex_nesting():
    complex_nested_json_string = """
    {
        "outer_key": [
            {
                "inner_key_1": "value1",
                "inner_key_2": {
                    "deep_key": "deep_value"

                }

            },
            {
                "inner_key_3": "value3"
            }
        ]
    }
    """
    output = JSON_WRAPPER_RE.match(complex_nested_json_string)
    print(f"output = {output}")
```

